==English==

===Etymology===
Old French [[replevir]] ‘recover’, from [[re-]] + [[plevir]] (probably from a Germanic source which also gave [[pledge]]).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/rɪ'plɛvi/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|replev|i|ed}}

# to [[return]] goods to their rightful owner by [[replevin]]; to [[recover]] goods